H. striatellata

is a rare species in the Central Paratethys; most specimens were found so far at the Hungarian locality Letkés. The documented distribution might point to a paleogeographic restriction to the southern Paratethyan basins and a stratigraphic restriction to the Langhian equivalent of the Badenian. Proto-Mediterranean Sea. Burdigalian (early Miocene): Torino Hills (
Sacco 1895
).
